{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d27fb73b-8b40-451c-8dc9-aeef2627fabb","content":"For a .NET Web API, use the `dotnet new webapi` template. Authentication options include:\n\n| Option | Flag |\n|---|---|\n| None (default) | `--auth None` |\n| Individual accounts | `--auth Individual` |\n| Microsoft identity platform | `--auth SingleOrg` |\n| Windows auth | `--auth Windows` |\n\n**Examples:**\n\n```bash\n# Basic API with JWT bearer auth (individual accounts)\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n\n# API with Azure AD / Entra ID auth\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --domain yourdomain.com -o MyApi\n```\n\nRun `dotnet new webapi --help` for the full list of options and parameters for your installed SDK version.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"4c44fb42-6510-4fb6-a798-754d31d6d54b","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about web API project templates and authentication options. This is a general knowledge question about .NET (likely, given the repository context with dotnet plugins). I can answer this from my knowledge without needing to look at files.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer about dotnet web API templates and authentication options.","outputTokens":260,"requestId":"A854:297498:44908CE:4AF9DA8:69F155F1"},"id":"28f46a30-70c2-4f56-b7c7-34cdbc8d4951","timestamp":"2026-04-29T00:51:05.578Z","parentId":"bd05698a-45ce-4f67-85da-7bc6532df042"}
